### What computer are you on (hardware)?

MBP 2.5 GHz Intel Core i7

### What operating system are you using, including version. e.g. Ubuntu 14.04? Fedora 23?

OSX 10.12.6 (Sierra)

### What version of BigchainDB software were you using?

I am seeing this error on Bigchain 2.0alpha1 ([v2.0.0a1](https://github.com/bigchaindb/bigchaindb/tree/v2.0.0a1)), and the current master branch (4 commits later: 8c1ee8329ecbff28f52b4540b5ad5f26c50b421e).

My docker versions:

```
$ docker -v
Docker version 18.03.0-ce, build 0520e24
$ docker-compose -v
docker-compose version 1.20.1, build 5d8c71b
```

### What, exactly, did you do to get to the point where you got stuck? Describe all the steps so we can get there too. 

I'm starting the BDB server from the source dir with:

```
docker container rm --force --volumes $(docker container ls --quiet --all)  
docker-compose build bigchaindb
docker-compose run -d bdb
```

Using the JS BDB driver `v4.0.0`, I am: 
- creating an asset pool with 10^18 tokens
- transferring tokens to (demo) users
- transferring tokens between users
- every time I transfer, I collect all UTXOs for that user into the inputs of the transaction
- **this works fine when the user has one or maybe a few UTXOs, but consistently fails when we are gathering 5+ UTXOs into a single transaction's inputs**

